{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ffa7bc3b-9209-4432-8ef5-ca3401b6ba8c","content":"Two things change with xUnit v3 + MTP:\n\n**1. Flag name:** `--filter` (VSTest syntax) → `--treenode-filter` (MTP syntax)\n\n**2. Expression syntax:** MTP uses a path/glob-based tree-node filter instead of VSTest's property expressions.\n\n| VSTest concept | MTP equivalent |\n|---|---|\n| `FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests` | `/**/*IntegrationTests*/**` (glob on the test tree path) |\n| `Category=Smoke` | `[Category=Smoke]` (trait as a property filter) |\n| `&` (AND) | combine path glob + property inline |\n\n**Translated command:**\n\n```bash\n# Old (VSTest / xUnit v2)\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n\n# New (MTP / xUnit v3)\ndotnet test --treenode-filter \"/**/*IntegrationTests*[Category=Smoke]/**\"\n```\n\nOr run the executable directly (MTP supports this):\n\n```bash\n./TestProject --treenode-filter \"/**/*IntegrationTests*[Category=Smoke]/**\"\n```\n\nThe `/**` at both ends ensures it matches at any depth in the test tree (assembly → namespace → class → method), and `[Category=Smoke]` filters nodes carrying that trait.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"cef961c3-3d11-4b47-a1df-679a8e00e967","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is migrating from xUnit v2 to xUnit v3 with Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). Let me explain the key differences in filtering.\n\nWith VSTest (xUnit v2), the filter syntax was:\n```\n--filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nWith MTP (xUnit v3), the filter syntax changes. MTP uses `--filter` but with a different syntax. The key changes:\n\n1. MTP uses `--treenode-filter` instead of `--filter` for the Microsoft.Testing.Platform runner\n2. The filter syntax changes from VSTest-style to MTP-style\n\n\n3. When using `dotnet test` with MTP, the `--filter` argument gets translated, though the semantics may differ from VSTest\n4. When running the test executable directly, you'd use MTP's native filter syntax instead\n\nMTP uses a different filter format altogether—tree-node filters with glob patterns like `/**/*IntegrationTests*/**[Category=Smoke]`, where VSTest's `FullyQualifiedName~X` becomes a glob pattern and `Category=Smoke` becomes a property filter in brackets. Recent SDK versions (9+) handle this translation automatically when you use `dotnet test`, but there's also a compatibility mode to be aware of. I'm working through the exact syntax for MTP's tree-node filter—it needs to match the test hierarchy (assembly > namespace > class > method) and apply trait filtering, so something like `/**/*IntegrationTests*[Category=Smoke]/**` should capture tests with \"IntegrationTests\" in their path and the Smoke category trait.","outputTokens":1423},"id":"913dc240-df52-4a8a-b8ad-44617b9e4a30","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:50:52.188Z","parentId":"8b9fcbbc-21c7-4d37-b1cc-99aa6c56b718"}
